  "notes": "Lao (Laotian). Tai-Kadai abugida closely related to Thai script. 6-tone language. Consonants in three classes (low/mid/high) interact with tone marks. Inherent vowel is /o/ (short). Simplified compared to Thai: no ช/ซ/ถ/ท distinctions — Lao merged many Thai letters.",
